Sie sind reich an Proteinen und Aminosäuren, um die Muskeln Ihres Haustieres zu stärken und zu erhalten. Die Omega-3-Fettsäuren sind ein Pluspunkt, um die Haut Ihres Haustieres mit glänzendem Fell gesund zu halten.

Es enthält auch Mineralstoffe, die zu starken Zähnen und Knochen beitragen.

Description group: Purina fügt Eiweiss in jedes Rezept ein - eine starke Grundlage für die Ernährung Ihres Haustieres.
title: Trockenei
Description: Das Trockeneiprodukt enthält das Eigelb und das Eiweiss, ohne die Schale. Es ist eine ausgezeichnete Quelle für Proteine und essentielle Aminosäuren, die die Muskeln Ihres Haustieres stärken. Es enthält auch Fette und Fettsäuren die für gesunde Haut und Fell beitragen.

Description group: Purina fügt Eiweiss in jedes Rezept ein - eine starke Grundlage für die Ernährung Ihres Haustieres.
title: Erbsenprotein
Description: Erbsenprotein ist der konzentrierte, proteinreiche Teil der Hülsenfrucht, der zur Stärkung und Erhaltung der Muskeln Ihres Haustieres beiträgt. Es ist ausserdem sehr gut verdaulich.

Description group: Purina fügt Eiweiss in jedes Rezept ein - eine starke Grundlage für die Ernährung Ihres Haustieres.
title: Sojamehl
Description: Sojamehl wird hergestellt, indem man das Öl aus den Sojabohnen entfernt und sie dann zu einem proteinreichen Bestandteil mahlt. Als hochwertige Proteinquelle hilft es, die Muskeln Ihres Haustieres zu stärken und zu erhalten. Es enthält einen guten Gehalt an essentiellen Aminosäuren wie Lysin und Mineralien wie Kalium.

Description group: Purina fügt Eiweiss in jedes Rezept ein - eine starke Grundlage für die Ernährung Ihres Haustieres.
title: Weizenglutenmehl
Description: Weizengluten ist der Eiweissteil des Weizenkorns, der bei der Trennung des stärkehaltigen Teils gewonnen wird, es besteht zu mindestens aus 80% wertvollen Proteinen und ist hochverdaulich, was zur Stärkung und Erhaltung der Muskulatur Ihres Haustieres beiträgt. Sein Aminosäureprofil ist eine gute Ergänzung zu Fleischproteinen.

Description group: Purina fügt Eiweiss in jedes Rezept ein - eine starke Grundlage für die Ernährung Ihres Haustieres.
title: Maisklebermehl
Description: Maisklebermehl wird durch Entfernen von Stärke und Keimen aus dem Maiskorn hergestellt, um einen proteinreichen Inhaltsstoff zu erhalten. Als gute Proteinquelle ist es reich an essentiellen Aminosäuren, die helfen, die Muskeln Ihres Haustieres zu stärken und zu erhalten.

Description group: Purina fügt Eiweiss in jedes Rezept ein - eine starke Grundlage für die Ernährung Ihres Haustieres.
title: Sojaprotein
Description: Sojaprotein ist ein Extrakt aus Sojabohnen mit hochwertigem Protein, das die Muskeln Ihres Haustieres stärkt und pflegt.

Description group: Purina fügt Eiweiss in jedes Rezept ein - eine starke Grundlage für die Ernährung Ihres Haustieres.
title: Hefe
Description: Hefe ist ein lebender, einzelliger Organismus, der von Natur aus fettarm ist, eine ausgezeichnete Proteinquelle (45%) darstellt und essentielle Aminosäuren wie Lysin, Methionin enthält. Es ist auch reich an B-Komplex-Vitaminen, die die allgemeine Körpergesundheit Ihres Haustieres unterstützen und reich an anderen Mineralien wie Kalzium, Phosphor und Eisen ist.

Description group: Purina fügt Eiweiss in jedes Rezept ein - eine starke Grundlage für die Ernährung Ihres Haustieres.
title: Pflanzliche Proteinextrakte
Description: Pflanzliche Proteinextrakte, wie z.B. Weizengluten, sind aus pflanzlichen Quellen angereicherte Proteine. Dieser Inhaltsstoff ist hochverdaulich, was zur Stärkung und Erhaltung der Muskeln Ihres Haustieres beiträgt. Sein Aminosäureprofil ist eine gute Ergänzungsquelle zu Fleischproteinen. In Nassfutter wird es auch verwendet, um die Textur des Futters zu verbessern, damit ihr Haustier die Mahlzeit geniessen können.

title: Wheat / Whole-grain Wheat
Description: Wheat grain is a natural and wholesome ingredient that is an excellent energy source for pets for their daily activity. The quality used is the same as wheat grain used in human food.

Description group: We only select carbohydrate sources that deliver sustaining energy to pets.
title: Whole Barley
Description: Whole barley is a natural and healthy ingredient that is a good source of carbohydrates that helps fuel your pet’s body for a healthy energy level. It's a nutrient dense source of fibre to support healthy digestion.

Description group: We only select carbohydrate sources that deliver sustaining energy to pets.
title: Oat
Description: Oat is a natural and healthy ingredient that is a good source of carbohydrates that helps fuel your pet’s body for a healthy energy level. It's a nutrient dense source of fibre to support healthy digestion.

Description group: We only select carbohydrate sources that deliver sustaining energy to pets.
title: Dried Cassava
Description: Cassava root also called manioc, is a plant cultivated for its starchy root in tropical and subtropical regions. This natural ingredient is used as alternative source of carbohydrates in grain free formulas. It’s created by drying the tuber and then grinding it down to a fine powder to create flour. It’s a highly digestible ingredient and a natural source of carbohydrates  to provide energy to help fuel your pet’s body.

Description group: We only select carbohydrate sources that deliver sustaining energy to pets.
title: Pea Starch
Description: Pea starch is derived from whole peas. As an alternative source of carbohydrates, it’s ideal for those who are seeking grain-free nutrition. It’s used to help fuel your pet’s body for healthy energy.

Description group: We only select carbohydrate sources that deliver sustaining energy to pets.
title: Linseed Meal
Description: Linseed meal is produce following the mechanical extraction of linseed oil. It is a rich source of carbohydrate and also fibre. it’s used to help fuel your pet’s body for healthy energy.

Description group: We only select carbohydrate sources that deliver sustaining energy to pets.
title: Wheat Middling/Fibre
Description: Wheat Middlings are obtained during wheat milling process. It is composed of a blend of wheat flour, germ and bran. It is a good source of carbohydrate to provide energy to help fuel your pet’s body.

Description group: We only select carbohydrate sources that deliver sustaining energy to pets.
title: Maize (Maize)
Description: Whole grain maize is a natural and healthy ingredient that is a good source of carbohydrate to provide energy to help fuel your pet's body.

Description group: We only select carbohydrate sources that deliver sustaining energy to pets.
title: Maize Grits
Description: Maize grits are made from maize kernels which have been dehulled and degermed during the milling process. It provides energy to help fuel your pet's body

Description group: We only select carbohydrate sources that deliver sustaining energy to pets.
title: Dried Beet Pulp
Description: Dried beet pulp is what remains after removing the sugar of the beet so the fiber-rich portion of the vegetable remains. It contributes to improve stool quality in your pet  and overall gastrointestinal health. In our cat formulas, beet pulp together with cellulose helps minimize the formation of hairballs by providing fibre.

Description group: We only select carbohydrate sources that deliver sustaining energy to pets.
title: Dried Chicory Root
Description: Chicory is a plant that grows naturally across Europe. The ingredient is obtained by washing, cutting & drying chicory roots. Chicory root contains high levels of inulin, a prebiotic proven to help improving digestive health in cats and dogs.

Description group: We only select carbohydrate sources that deliver sustaining energy to pets.
title: Corn (Maize) Starch
Description: Corn (maize) starch is a healthy ingredient used in dry pet food as a good source of carbohydrate to provide energy to help fuel your pet's body.

Description group: We only select carbohydrate sources that deliver sustaining energy to pets.
title: Cellulose
Description: Powdered cellulose is derived from the pulp of fiber-rich plants. Cellulose improves stool quality in your dog and cat.  In cat formulas, it helps minimize the formation of hairballs.

Description group: We only source nutrient-rich fats and oils, with known benefits for pets.
title: Animal Fat
Description: Animal fats are obtained from either pork or beef fatty body part. They are also produced from chicken or turkey. They are highly digestible. Just like protein, fat is a beneficial component to the pet diet for growth and development. Animal fats provide essential fatty acids such as omega-6 for a healthy skin and coat as well as an excellent source of energy to your pet (more than protein). They also help the absorption of  fat-soluble vitamins in the body.

Description group: We only source nutrient-rich fats and oils, with known benefits for pets.
title: Poultry Fat
Description: Poultry fat is obtained from the fatty body parts of the chicken or turkey and it's highly digestible. They are highly digestible. Just like protein, fat is a beneficial component to the pet diet for growth and development and  provide essential fatty acids such as omega-6 for a healthy skin and coat as well as an excellent source of energy to your pet (more than protein). They also help the absorption of  fat-soluble vitamins in the body.

Description group: We only source nutrient-rich fats and oils, with known benefits for pets.
title: Lard
Description: Lard  is obtained from pork fatty body part. It is highly digestible. Just like protein, fat is a beneficial component to the pet diet for growth and development. It provides essential fatty acids such as omega-6 for a healthy skin and coat as well as an excellent source of energy to your pet (more than protein). They also help the absorption of  fat-soluble vitamins in the body.

Description group: We only source nutrient-rich fats and oils, with known benefits for pets.
title: Fish Oil
Description: Fish oil is produced from fish like salmon. It has a high level of omega-3 fatty acids which are well know to keep shiny coat but also support a healthy immune system. Amongst the omega-3 fatty acids found in fish oil, EPA promotes pet’s healthy joints, skin and coat. DHA, also well present in fish oil, contributes to a healthy vision and is an important promoter for the brain development in puppies and kittens.

Description group: We only source nutrient-rich fats and oils, with known benefits for pets.
title: Linseed Oil
Description: Linseed oil, also known as flaxseed oil or flax oil, is a vegetable oil extracted from mature seeds of the flax plant. The oil is obtained by pressing the seeds and it is a good source of the omega-3 fatty acid (alpha linolenic) which helps to nourish your pet's skin and coat.

title: Olive oil
Description: Olive oil is a natural ingredient recognised as one of the critical components of the Mediterranean diet. It contains a high level of oleic acid, a monounsaturated fatty acid. Olive oil is known for its defensive properities.

title: Glycerol
Description: Glycerol (or glycerin) is a colorless, odorless, viscous liquid that is sweet-tasting and absolutely non-toxic. Glycerol is generally obtained from oleaginous plants where it occurs as triglycerides. It is widely used in the food industry as a sweetener or moisturizing agent, in our formulations, it allows to produce soft and chewy kibbles.

title: Propylene Glycol
Description: Propylene glycol is a  safe ingredient used in the food industry as a carrier for flavour systems or as a moisturizing agent to maintain texture stability for the whole shelf life.  In our dog food, this is important for our tender  chunks and ensures they remain fresh.

Description group: We harness the power of functional ingredients to support pet health.
SEO ALT image tag: L. Delbrueckii and fermentum to strengthen cat's defences
title: L. Delbrueckii and Fermentum
Description: Lactobacillus Delbrueckii and Fermentum are beneficial functional bacteria providing key nutrients proven to strengthen cats' natural defences.

Description group: We harness the power of functional ingredients to support pet health.
title: Spirulina
Description: Spirulina (Arthrospira platensis) is a blue green algae rich in proteins, beta carotene, antioxydants and omega 6 fatty acid. Spirulina helps supporting healthy immune function in cats and dogs.

Description group: We harness the power of functional ingredients to support pet health.
SEO ALT image tag: Taurine for healthy cat central nervous systems
title: Taurine
Description: Taurine is an essential nutrient for cats to be brought by the diet because they can't synthetise it. Cat food must contain the right amount of taurine to ensure and maintain a heathly metabolism. It is essential for cardiovascular, retina, and central nervous system functions. In dog food, taurine also helps support cardiac health.
SEO ALT benefit image tag 1: Support bright eyes and vision infographic

Description group: We harness the power of functional ingredients to support pet health.
title: Bentonite
Description: Bentonite is a natural clay added to sensitive products to bind excess water and help to improve faecal quality.

Description group: We harness the power of functional ingredients to support pet health.
title: Dried Colostrum
Description: Colostrum is first milk of the cow after she gives birth to the calf. The calf takes what he needs and then the remaining colostrum is collected. It contains immunoglobulins and other proteins that help to build and strenghten immunity and also  promote a healthy intestinal microbiome.

Description group: We curate balanced combinations of vitamins based on a variety of nutritional profiles.
SEO ALT image tag: Vitamin A to support overall pet health
title: Vitamin A
Description: Vitamin A is essential in supporting your pet’s vision, immune system, bone and muscle growth and skin and coat health.

Description group: We curate balanced combinations of vitamins based on a variety of nutritional profiles.
SEO ALT image tag: Vitamin D to support overall pet health
title: Vitamin D
Description: Vitamin D is necessary for normal bone tissue growth and maintenance. It plays an important role in supporting your pet’s teeth, bones and joints.

Description group: We curate balanced combinations of vitamins based on a variety of nutritional profiles.
SEO ALT image tag: Vitamin E to support overall pet health
title: Vitamin E
Description: Vitamin E is an essential vitamin that functions also as an antioxidant to help support your pet’s immune system, while also nourishing your pet’s skin and coat.

Description group: We curate balanced combinations of vitamins based on a variety of nutritional profiles.
SEO ALT image tag: Vitamin C to support natural defences
title: Vitamin C
Description: Vitamin C is a water soluble vitamin that acts as an antioxidant, helping to reduce free radical formation and supporting pets' natural defences.

Description group: Minerals are essential to ensure a healthy and balanced diet.
SEO ALT image tag: Ferrous sulphate monohydrate for overall health
title: Ferrous Sulphate Monohydrate
Description: Ferrous sulfate monohydrate is a source of iron, an essential trace mineral needed for hemoglobin production and oxygen transport from your pet’s lungs throughout their whole body.

title: Zinc Sulphate Monohydrate
Description: Zinc sulfate monohydrate is a source of zinc, an essential trace mineral. It is needed to promote healthy skin and a shiny coat. It also helps support a healthy immune system and aids in the metabolism of carbohydrates, fat and protein.

title: Sodium Selenite
Description: Sodium selenite is a source of selenium, an essential trace mineral that works as an antioxidant and helps maintain your pet’s cell membranes in conjunction with the immune system.

title: Tocopherol extracts
